5.3 Example 5.7

5.3.1 Load data

ts &lt;- 
  read_excel("data/J13.xlsx", skip = 1) |&gt; 
  mutate(t = row_number()) |&gt; 
  tsibble(index = t)



5.3.2 Estimate AR(2) with first 200 observations

fit &lt;- 
  ts |&gt; 
  filter(t &lt;= 200) |&gt; 
  model(AR = AR(Z ~ order(2)))

Coefficients:

tidy(fit)

# A tibble: 2 × 6
  .model term  estimate std.error statistic  p.value
  &lt;chr&gt;  &lt;chr&gt;    &lt;dbl&gt;     &lt;dbl&gt;     &lt;dbl&gt;    &lt;dbl&gt;
1 AR     ar1      0.479    0.0663      7.23 1.02e-11
2 AR     ar2      0.344    0.0665      5.17 5.62e- 7


Model statistics:

glance(fit)

# A tibble: 1 × 6
  .model sigma2   AIC  AICc   BIC   dof
  &lt;chr&gt;   &lt;dbl&gt; &lt;dbl&gt; &lt;dbl&gt; &lt;dbl&gt; &lt;int&gt;
1 AR      0.617 -177. -177. -171.   198




5.3.3 Time series cross-validation

ts_cv &lt;- 
  ts |&gt; 
  stretch_tsibble(.step = 1, .init = 200) |&gt; 
  filter(.id != max(.id))

ts_cv |&gt; 
  model(AR = AR(Z ~ order(2))) |&gt; 
  forecast(h = 1) |&gt; 
  accuracy(ts)

